d-animal life-years caused per human DALY, times the suffering per factory-farmed life-year, times the animal&#x27;s welfare range. Under a heavy animal welfare range the penalty can exceed the human benefit, so saving human lives looks net-harmful. Only bites once animals count, so it requires animals_somewhat; and it is a near-term human-vs-animal get-off point, not combined with astronomical-stakes longtermism (no_discounting_future_humans), where x-risk dominates and the meat bookkeeping is moot. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 5 animals_matter_a_lot → 6 suffering_focused → 7 meat_eater_problem" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylVmFv2kgQ%2FSuj6E5HuIQYk0DhxAdCaBuVXiuSu%2BpUKnexx3gv611rdx2HpvnvN2tDgAB3lQ4JYbwzb2bezL7dx6MIY5YLO1QRHvWOzs6g3%2B%2FDrWZcglUQavZtQQ%2BFhGnue81zKJQW0T3HAopm4Aet4CJoBx2oGasy6Bw796kkmIExeZpZriSECaH1wIOMaRUmnAkH1uz60ISY6YAVbBEkecqkWS34wCRPmTCBUSkWCbOrlRbEuc01Lh2ClFmLOii4TYKIm1Dl0nI5X5lfPAMtDVkg1DNYG0wex6jJIYhVmBuMVksdSJHZgL7klGk1E5iWhY1YmABbV8cNMPi4sAk9x1wgEHPrZXMG1mXPosicgEaim0s0oHQJpvGUSGEpUhRu6L1NsOLrF0OFyrDE%2BA1ClWbKuLqeDchXRkiI9IqbEs1YJiMmlERIqZ%2BiAV%2Bf2zW6%2F%2BpSde74kGFoyfGeiRxBxSXCurONEuwSjYVZvoDchXGOBjcL68FNonmawScU1EWEj1r9TbiV95vR76PJ4HZ0BbMFzFGiJiIb2WI1Rhhxu0VTnRZPQFJvymQck4RUYl1xTbiA1Cn6IZrRtUDpOXGUUQpML2BGIWIecno%2BgcvR6w%2BTEXGgmSgRCuTzxI0FMSKUG%2ByEf606J9RcKk0TAl3vZxheQ01pqvdUxacpm0tu8wjh8sPtaHhM%2BRiVZ%2B%2B4DROUV0wsPqL%2Bw0TQh8epBMhQZQLfosgwel7xGt6FC%2Bg1LpxNgULMkDJ5Qy10EJWJ16xsvKYzKocYdcxCmzNxyeTdn2WnnGnrQKT6Hug61JpwegjueCqfpnIebRXicvHOl8l4%2FlSyNN4xaC0r8nxKl%2FF0x2BVjU8120RsrTcbvls97xCbRba95HueW%2BucUxJTWXARzfK52bZpVzav%2FNKGCRFjtKcXg7nmIQlbTjMwZJYZq1WWIFkNUdLbFfGtZapldwS%2FR3PD7ktWr5QQTF%2FHG96VT5m%2F7%2ByjKu6Yx26p5ZWRh%2FyeC%2F6Nubkeycg1hGDlDsxqLsqW0%2B6%2Fu0loG00wVZvxXcl42ixrpgev66wrCXRVm4G9sezOQTa99ae09l58fpCX%2Bn%2FTUN%2Bq%2FNcfQ%2F0RYur%2FQkR9T9nlCJMGFkrtGYKHCYFNMMrDXUJbS0Kb%2Fv8jdH%2BMg7lWR8jn4mow%2FguIYe10OCN9%2FelLb1PXoi3Nszxdng1rTQsVLZLiEb8v9Jvc2YvTF7LcGied3OkznZLu3OjDZ1fBI9Amxx5Mj8YqJB10Ggd3lchNj06giJ6J7blDUdb2quAxFU3yRNNQOy1VpNXptprtY3g62Y7iml5Juljsx9%2FUpB3Ydrt77vn7YekoEuAuIlS05nYBtcH718f7g2wJm4uyjtFue%2F6r5m6IwfV7OIPhEnskrcaMTmHMtUl4diDMpjy%2BLOaidfHqfDfOLTX6rbveIIyRzXPcD72lrBV0t9veQdt%2FTB%2Fo7KYiV5Bet7UD%2BYmUme45hnAM1JIq1YwuDDSPEZoDjO%2Fq%2BTLCboDBePx6dHWA0ReSX%2FaOlLGzp19gWIxuDiaVRsCEbjFMh8mBFHekpMywBP7iNq%2Bmw9Pdwvow5sY2NNIONlgr%2Fxil7eWiVm2uE3j8%2FvAdHhobMZ6O6ciduWtVH5ZAn70vS0243Xsxu317fbPe2D0ob8KcSJ%2BtbmckGZyyMLStN%2B56FMFZbEafyqOnfwCkOwLm" id="w1_2_3_5_6_7"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#eec2a8;strokeColor=#c65a2e;fontColor=#5a2a10;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1261" y="956" width="244" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Net-negative lives&lt;br&gt;(animal suffering dominates)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+5+6+7+8]&lt;br&gt;→ Shrimp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;(Brian Tomasik, David Benatar)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + animals_matter_a_lot + suffering_focused + meat_eater_problem + net_negative_animal_lives&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The net-negative-lives hypothesis: factory-farmed and wild animals endure more suffering than wellbeing, so their lives are not worth living. Reducing that suffering is worth more per dollar (you are mitigating a catastrophe, not improving a good life), most of all for the astronomical wild-invertebrate populations. Combined with the meat-eater problem it drives human charities firmly net-negative — every human sustained means more net-negative farmed lives. Presupposes counting wild/invertebrate animals, so it requires animals_matter_a_lot; and like the meat-eater problem it is a near-term animal get-off point, not combined with astronomical-stakes longtermism (no_discounting_future_humans). || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discountin