html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#c9b3dd;strokeColor=#4a2a78;fontColor=#201040;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1652" y="1434" width="200" height="108" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Meat-eater problem&lt;br&gt;(saved humans eat animals)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+3+5+7]&lt;br&gt;→ Shrimp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;(Michael Dickens, Vasco Grilo)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + future_humans_matter_with_discounting + animals_matter_a_lot + meat_eater_problem&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The meat-eater problem: a dollar of human global health also buys decades of that person&#x27;s meat consumption, and factory farming it causes suffering the animal circle now counts. Each present-human org is charged an additive penalty — farmed-animal life-years caused per human DALY, times the suffering per factory-farmed life-year, times the animal&#x27;s welfare range. Under a heavy animal welfare range the penalty can exceed the human benefit, so saving human lives looks net-harmful. Only bites once animals count, so it requires animals_somewhat; and it is a near-term human-vs-animal get-off point, not combined with astronomical-stakes longtermism (no_discounting_future_humans), where x-risk dominates and the meat bookkeeping is moot. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 3 future_humans_matter_with_discounting → 5 animals_matter_a_lot → 7 meat_eater_problem" link="https://www.squiggle-language.com/playground#code=eJylVmFv2kgQ%2FSuj6E4HXEJsk5CGEx8IoW1Ueq1I7qpTqehij%2FFe1rvW7joOTfPfb9aGBIK5q3RICOOdfTPzZvbNPhxEGLNc2KGK8KB3cHwM%2FX4fbjTjEqyCULNvS3ooJEzzwPNPoFBaRHccCyj8WTDrzE5nZ9AwVmVw1nSbp5JABsbkaWa5khAmhNUDDzKmVZhwJhyUfx6ADzHTM1aw5SzJUybNeiEAJnnKhJkZlWKRMLte6UCc21zjasMsZdainhXcJrOIm1Dl0nK5WJufPgGtDNlMqCewM0iR2Rl9aSXTai4wLaMfsTAB9pwCN8Dg49Im9BxzgUDkPC%2BbY7AuRBZF5hA0EqNcogGlSzCNR5Q5S5G8cEPvbYIVKb8YykaGJcZvEKo0U8YF%2F2RAe2WEhEivuCnRjGUyYkJJhJRKJtrw9akio7uvLlS3He8zDC1tvGMiR1BxifBcvHYJdoHGwjxfQu7cuI0GNxPrwXWieZrBJxRUKo